# Repository Pattern & Dependency Injection Guide

You are an expert in repository pattern implementation and dependency injection for Crystal applications.

## Repository Pattern Architecture

### Core Repository Interface
Located in [src/circed/core/interfaces.cr](mdc:src/circed/core/interfaces.cr):

```crystal
module Core
  module Repository(T)
    abstract def add(id : String, entity : T) : Void
    abstract def get(id : String) : T?
    abstract def remove(id : String) : Bool
    abstract def all : Array(T)
    abstract def size : Int32
    abstract def clear : Void
  end
end
```

### Repository Implementation Pattern
All repositories in [src/circed/repositories/](mdc:src/circed/repositories/) follow this pattern:

```crystal
module Circed
  module Repositories
    class EntityRepository
      include Core::Repository(Domain::Entity)
      
      @@entities = Hash(String, Domain::Entity).new
      
      def add(id : String, entity : Domain::Entity) : Void
        @@entities[id] = entity
      end
      
      def get(id : String) : Domain::Entity?
        @@entities[id]?
      end
      
      def remove(id : String) : Bool
        !@@entities.delete(id).nil?
      end
      
      def all : Array(Domain::Entity)
        @@entities.values
      end
      
      def size : Int32
        @@entities.size
      end
      
      def clear : Void
        @@entities.clear
      end
    end
  end
end
```

## Dependency Injection Container

### Container Implementation
Located in [src/circed/infrastructure/container.cr](mdc:src/circed/infrastructure/container.cr):

```crystal
module Infrastructure
  class Container
    alias ServiceInstance = Repositories::UserRepository | 
                           Repositories::ChannelRepository | 
                           Repositories::ServerRepository | 
                           Services::AuthenticationService | 
                           Services::NotificationService | 
                           Services::IRCService

    @@instances = Hash(String, ServiceInstance).new

    def self.register(type : T.class, instance : T) forall T
      @@instances[type.name] = instance.as(ServiceInstance)
    end

    def self.resolve(type : T.class) : T forall T
      instance = @@instances[type.name]?
      raise "Service #{type.name} not registered" unless instance
      instance.as(T)
    end
  end
end
```

### Service Locator Pattern
```crystal
module Infrastructure
  module ServiceLocator
    def self.user_repository
      Container.resolve(Repositories::UserRepository)
    end

    def self.channel_repository
      Container.resolve(Repositories::ChannelRepository)
    end

    def self.server_repository
      Container.resolve(Repositories::ServerRepository)
    end

    def self.authentication_service
      Container.resolve(Services::AuthenticationService)
    end

    def self.notification_service
      Container.resolve(Services::NotificationService)
    end

    def self.irc_service
