## Best Practices

### Repository Design
- Keep repositories focused on data access
- Use class variables (`@@`) for shared state
- Implement all interface methods
- Provide domain-specific methods beyond basic CRUD

### Service Design
- Inject dependencies through constructor
- Keep services stateless when possible
- Use services for complex business logic
- Coordinate between multiple repositories

### Container Usage
- Register all services at startup
- Use service locator for accessing dependencies
- Keep container interface simple
- Avoid circular dependencies

### Error Handling
```crystal
def get_required_service(type : T.class) : T forall T
  service = Container.resolve(type)
  raise "Required service #{type.name} not available" unless service
  service
end
```

### Memory Management
- Clear repositories in tests
- Clean up empty collections
- Use efficient data structures
- Monitor memory usage in long-running processes

## Domain Entity Integration

### Entity Creation
```crystal
# Create domain entities through repositories
user = Domain::User.new(nickname, username, hostname, realname, servername)
user_repository.add(nickname, user)

channel = Domain::Channel.new(channel_name)
channel_repository.add(channel_name, channel)
```

### Entity Lifecycle
- Repositories manage entity persistence
- Services coordinate entity interactions
- Actions handle entity state changes
- Domain entities contain business logic

### Data Consistency
- Use repositories for all data access
- Maintain referential integrity
- Handle cascading deletes properly
- Validate state transitions
